ROBERT SHILLER:
I'm all confused.

00:03:41.840 --> 00:03:44.810
I'm talking to an
organization in transition.

00:03:44.810 --> 00:03:46.530
I don't know how to.

00:03:46.530 --> 00:03:49.640
But I was thinking, I think of
you as a search engine company,

00:03:49.640 --> 00:03:51.820
but that's very narrow.

00:03:51.820 --> 00:03:54.390
But I think maybe it's better
to think of you as a marketing

00:03:54.390 --> 00:03:55.870
company.

00:03:55.870 --> 00:03:57.450
Is that a good?

00:03:57.450 --> 00:04:01.500
You're a big data company,
and we have mixed feelings

00:04:01.500 --> 00:04:02.752
about all of these things.

00:04:02.752 --> 00:04:04.640
[LAUGHTER]

00:04:04.640 --> 00:04:07.550
So I thought I should start
by saying that I've already

00:04:07.550 --> 00:04:12.160
thought of Google as an
ethical company in this space.

00:04:12.160 --> 00:04:14.390
So just did a test this morning.

00:04:14.390 --> 00:04:18.660
I went on to
news.google.com, and I just

00:04:18.660 --> 00:04:20.279
looked at what came up.

00:04:20.279 --> 00:04:23.240
And there was, the way
my computer does it,

00:04:23.240 --> 00:04:28.350
I saw a big news story
about Hurricane Patrick,

00:04:28.350 --> 00:04:30.770
which is the biggest
hurricane ever that's

00:04:30.770 --> 00:04:32.480
